The paper discusses entity resolution, which is a problem commonly studied in the database community (cs.DB). The proposed solution involves using generative models and expectation maximization, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of similarity vectors, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
